						<summary>

						<p>The inscription is damaged and refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Trailōkyamalladēva (Sōmēśvara I).</hi> It seems to register a gift of land made to the god Akkēśvara of Sūṇḍi by Perggaḍe <hi rend="bold">Nāgadēvayya</hi> and other officers assembled at the <hi rend="italic">nelevīḍu</hi> <hi rend="bold">Vikramapura,</hi> while <hi rend="bold">Akkādēvī</hi> was governing <hi rend="bold">Kisukāḍu Seventy, Toṟagare Sixty</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Māsiyavāḍi One Hundred and Forty.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record is <hi rend="bold">dated Śaka 976, Jaya, Jyēshṭha, amāvāsyā, Tuesday, solar eclipse,</hi> The date corresponds to <hi rend="bold">Tuesday, 10th May, A.D. 1054.</hi> The month Jyēshṭha was <hi rend="italic">pūrṇimānta</hi> in this case.</p>						

						<p>(Published in <hi rend="italic">Ep. Ind.</hi> Vol. XV, pp. 80 ff).</p>						

						<p>The following corrections in the text may, however, be noted:—</p>						

